The paper discusses the design of algorithms for combinatorial problems, specifically Dominating Set, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics). The use of measure and conquer as a tool in algorithm design suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The mathematical analysis of the algorithm involves quasiconvex programming, which is a topic in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of computer aided algorithm design suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
